Taiga people

Surprisingly near the Mongolian capital Ulaanbaatar, the Gobi gradually begins to appear. Equally close are the southernmost reaches of the boreal forests of Siberia, which extends in an uninterrupted way all the way to Europe. Within small distances we will experience the diverse landscapes of Mongolia and meet the nomadic people that call these landscapes home.
